#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
Autonomous Task Orchestrator — Production Edition
=================================================
A fully concurrent, persistent, observable, and safe autonomous execution engine.

Architecture:
  - Concurrent execution via asyncio.Semaphore-bounded worker pool
  - SQLite-backed persistence with WAL mode (crash-safe, restart-recoverable)
  - Per-type circuit breakers (CLOSED → OPEN → HALF_OPEN state machine)
  - Exponential backoff with full jitter (AWS algorithm) for retries
  - Topological sort dependency resolution (O(V+E) Kahn's algorithm)
  - Binary min-heap priority scheduling (O(log n) task selection)
  - Event bus with lifecycle hooks (pub/sub over asyncio.Queue)
  - Structured JSON audit log (correlation-ID threaded)
  - In-process metrics registry (counters, gauges, histograms)
  - Plugin executor registry (task type → async callable handler)
  - Graceful shutdown with in-flight drain and state flush
  - Dead Letter Queue for permanently failed tasks with forensic metadata
  - Optional HTTP health endpoint (aiohttp, feature-flagged)

Dependencies (stdlib only unless HTTP health server is enabled):
  asyncio, sqlite3, json, heapq, logging, time, uuid, dataclasses,
  enum, collections, contextlib, signal, typing, pathlib, math, os

  Optional: aiohttp (pip install aiohttp) for /health /metrics /tasks endpoints
"""

